00:52:43,618 --> 00:52:46,705
You still look like
you're in your thirties.

794
00:52:47,372 --> 00:52:48,582
I am in my thirties.

795
00:52:50,709 --> 00:52:52,377
Exactly. You look like it.

796
00:52:52,460 --> 00:52:53,670
I see.

797
00:52:55,213 --> 00:52:57,507
Why are you here?
Are you here to see Ji-ung?

798
00:52:57,591 --> 00:52:59,009
Where is he?

799
00:52:59,092 --> 00:53:01,887
He and Chae-ran are practically living
in the editing room.

800
00:53:01,970 --> 00:53:03,930
-Follow me. I'll take you there.
-Okay.

801
00:53:04,014 --> 00:53:07,225
Gosh. I see that you've really made it.

802
00:53:07,309 --> 00:53:09,853
Even though you had
the lowest grades in school,

803
00:53:09,936 --> 00:53:13,106
I saw your potential
when I saw your drawings.

804
00:53:13,189 --> 00:53:15,901
-Gosh. How are your parents doing?
-They're doing well.

805
00:53:16,818 --> 00:53:19,237
Chae-ran. Where's Ji-ung?

806
00:53:19,321 --> 00:53:22,824
He just left to stop by his house.

807
00:53:22,908 --> 00:53:24,576
I see. Is he coming back?

808
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:27,746
He said it won't take long.
He'll be back soon.

809
00:53:28,747 --> 00:53:29,581
Is that so?

810
00:53:29,664 --> 00:53:32,918
Ung, wait here. Ji-ung will be back soon.

811
00:53:33,001 --> 00:53:34,377
-Okay.
-Good.

812
00:53:34,461 --> 00:53:36,296
Chae-ran, come out for a minute.

813
00:53:36,379 --> 00:53:37,839
-I have something to say.
-Okay.

814
00:53:42,761 --> 00:53:44,471
Gosh.

815
00:53:47,057 --> 00:53:48,266
What?

816
00:53:55,023 --> 00:53:56,608
What do I need to press?

817
00:54:10,038 --> 00:54:12,791
Exactly how slow do I need to be?

818
00:54:12,874 --> 00:54:14,334
MR. CHOI UNG

819
00:54:15,251 --> 00:54:17,128
Should I call or not?

820
00:54:24,552 --> 00:54:25,971
Hello?

821
00:54:27,305 --> 00:54:28,348
What?

822
00:54:30,934 --> 00:54:32,227
Okay. I'll check.

823
00:54:36,982 --> 00:54:38,775
Please pick up this time around.

824
00:54:41,069 --> 00:54:45,198
Gosh. I can't believe
my eyes are still red.

825
00:54:46,491 --> 00:54:48,410
I'm never going to cry again.

826
00:54:58,086 --> 00:55:00,547
-What is it?
-Are you still working?

827
00:55:01,464 --> 00:55:03,550
No, I clocked out on the dot.

828
00:55:03,633 --> 00:55:05,927
Well… Are you okay?

829
00:55:06,469 --> 00:55:07,470
What do you mean?

830
00:55:08,096 --> 00:55:09,639
Did you not read the news?

831
00:55:10,974 --> 00:55:12,017
About what?

832
00:55:12,100 --> 00:55:15,270
It's about NJ's dating rumor.

833
00:55:15,353 --> 00:55:16,688
Ji-ung?

834
00:55:16,771 --> 00:55:17,981
The thing is…

835
00:55:18,064 --> 00:55:19,649
-Hold on.
-Ung--

836
00:55:20,442 --> 00:55:22,152
It is you.

837
00:55:23,278 --> 00:55:24,738
Are you headed home?

838
00:55:27,032 --> 00:55:28,450
You must have left work early.

839
00:55:33,955 --> 00:55:37,250
I'm in a hurry,
so I should get going. Goodbye.

840
00:55:45,425 --> 00:55:48,428
Did something happen?

841
00:55:52,307 --> 00:55:53,349
Yeon-su.

842
00:55:55,143 --> 00:55:56,019
Yes?

843
00:55:57,228 --> 00:55:58,438
Today's my birthday.

844
00:55:59,814 --> 00:56:01,858
Oh, really?

845
00:56:02,484 --> 00:56:05,862
Happy birthday. Had I known sooner,
I would have treated you to a meal.

846
00:56:08,031 --> 00:56:10,492
My mom came by
and prepared a birthday meal.

847
00:56:11,910 --> 00:56:13,703
She's the woman I saw before, right?

848
00:56:14,954 --> 00:56:17,749
That was my first time seeing her.
She's really beautiful.

849
00:56:21,044 --> 00:56:22,462
She still doesn't know…

850
00:56:25,799 --> 00:56:28,134
that I'm allergic to peaches.

851
00:56:33,973 --> 00:56:35,141
One time…

852
00:56:37,769 --> 00:56:39,187
I almost died…

853
00:56:42,065 --> 00:56:44,567
in front of her after eating a peach.

854
00:56:46,194 --> 00:56:48,279
But I guess she still doesn't know.

855
00:56:50,115 --> 00:56:52,492
Hey. Ji-ung…

856
00:56:59,582 --> 00:57:01,417
Are you okay?

857
00:57:04,045 --> 00:57:05,922
Or is it that she doesn't want to know?

858
00:57:33,867 --> 00:57:35,994
CURRENT AFFAIRS AND CULTURE
KIM JI-UNG

859
00:57:40,999 --> 00:57:44,627
EPILOGUE
NOVEMBER, 2010

860
00:57:54,429 --> 00:57:56,055
Why are you standing here?

861
00:57:57,932 --> 00:58:00,059
Can I sleep over at your house today?

862
00:58:01,102 --> 00:58:02,187
Sure, you can.

863
00:58:23,374 --> 00:58:25,084
Isn't it much warmer now?

864
00:58:29,297 --> 00:58:30,715
How can he do that?

865
00:58:31,424 --> 00:58:33,092
-Unbelievable.
-I know, right?

866
00:58:34,219 --> 00:58:36,346
-Are you sleepy?
-No.

867
00:58:49,192 --> 00:58:52,362
THE PREVIOUS NIGHT

868
00:58:54,447 --> 00:58:55,865
Shouldn't you be working?

869
00:58:56,449 --> 00:58:57,951
Gosh.

870
00:59:02,539 --> 00:59:03,790
Tell me.

871
00:59:04,624 --> 00:59:05,625
About what?

872
00:59:05,708 --> 00:59:07,752
I'm all ears, so spill.

873
00:59:13,967 --> 00:59:14,968
My mom came by.

874
00:59:22,976 --> 00:59:24,978
She came unannounced again.

875
00:59:28,231 --> 00:59:31,818
Judging by the size of her suitcase,
I think she'll be here for a week.

876
00:59:33,903 --> 00:59:35,947
She'll act as if
she'll be staying with me.

877
00:59:37,657 --> 00:59:39,033
Then she'll vanish again.

878
00:59:41,536 --> 00:59:43,746
Gosh. How many times has she done this?

879
00:59:45,999 --> 00:59:48,459
She even made breakfast this morning.

880
00:59:48,543 --> 00:59:49,836
I can't believe her.

881
00:59:55,550 --> 01:00:02,557
HELLO, MY SOUL MATE

882
01:00:25,413 --> 01:00:27,999
She's pretty, but she's not Ung's type.

883
01:00:28,625 --> 01:00:31,794
What's the probability of your ex

884
01:00:31,878 --> 01:00:33,171
in your lifetime?

885
01:00:33,755 --> 01:00:35,256
Someone told me

886
01:00:35,340 --> 01:00:37,842
that everything I shoot
is full of emotions.

887
01:00:38,926 --> 01:00:42,096
About how you wanted us to be friends…

888
01:00:42,180 --> 01:00:44,015
I don't think I can do that.

889
01:00:44,098 --> 01:00:45,475
You're drunk.

890
01:00:45,558 --> 01:00:49,312
I don't think I can ever face

891
01:00:51,147 --> 01:00:52,190
The two of you…

892
01:00:53,066 --> 01:00:54,942
As you've read in the articles,

893
01:00:55,026 --> 01:00:57,236
we're seeing each other.

894
01:00:59,113 --> 01:01:04,118
Subtitle translation by: Soo-ji Kim
